<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1129" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1129">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14592.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Garrett</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 20, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your March 14, 8 p.m. State of Texas having consented, permission is
                            hereby granted General Ricaut to transport wounded soldiers to
                            Matamoros. Cost of transportation over Texas soil and other expenses to
                            be borne by General Ricaut.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>